{
  "texts": [
    "Students can also share a link to their interactions so that instructors can take a look at student explanations and note any gaps or sticking points in student understanding.",
    "Additionally, students can be asked to note any bias in AI responses and any specific hallucinations they spotted during the interactions.",
    "Students should report out the entire interaction and write a paragraph reflecting about the experience.",
    "That reflection can also serve as a basis for a class discussion that serves a dual purpose: a discussion about the topic or concept and about how to work with the AI.",
    "While the risks of teaching an AI student are low, there are some elements of the exercise to watch out for."
  ]
}